<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-23T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="751" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857Ar1/24a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-23T11:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1915, 11 a. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2105. Please informally inquire of the Foreign Office whether any
                                report has been made to the German Government on the torpedoing and
                                sinking of the British steamship <hi rend="italic">Arabic.</hi>
                                Without inviting an explanation you should give <persName corresp="#p_JGEGV1">Von Jagow</persName> an opportunity to
                                explain the attack which we are advised was without warning. Report
                                fully the substance of your conversation.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>